    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-03-14T21:18:04+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-14T21:18:04+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-14T10:48:04Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-14T10:48:04Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A trough over inland WA is expected to move across western and northern SA on Sunday and continues northeast early in the week. A ridge of high pressure persists over the south. A cold front clips the southeast early next week.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW014" description="North East Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-03-14T21:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-15T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-14T10:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-14T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly clear. Winds east to southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-03-15T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-16T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-14T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-15T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower west of Leigh Creek in the evening. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm near the eastern border in the late afternoon and evening. Winds east to southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h turning north to northeasterly 20 to 30 km/h during the morning then tending northeast to southeasterly in the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 17 and 26 with daytime temperatures reaching the mid to high 30s.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 9:50am to 5:00pm, UV Index predicted to reach 11 [Extreme]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-03-16T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-17T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-15T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-16T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Very high chance of rain west of Leigh Creek, medium chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm west of Leigh Creek in the late afternoon and evening, possibly severe with heavy rain which may lead to flash flooding. Winds northeast to southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h tending north to northeasterly 25 to 35 km/h in the early morning then tending northeast to southeasterly 20 to 30 km/h in the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to 21 to 27 with daytime temperatures reaching 26 to 36.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-03-17T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-18T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-16T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-17T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Very high chance of rain north of Leigh Creek, medium chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm north of Leigh Creek. Winds northeast to southeasterly 25 to 35 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 18 and 25 with daytime temperatures reaching 24 to 33.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-03-18T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-19T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-17T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-18T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. High chance of showers, most likely in the morning and afternoon. The chance of a thunderstorm north of Leigh Creek. Winds east to southeasterly 20 to 30 km/h tending south to southeasterly during the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to between 18 and 24 with daytime temperatures reaching 25 to 30.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
